# Methodology

A software development methodology is a process by which developers design, implement and test new software projects.

&nbsp;

## Example

- How to develop and test project
- How to release the project
- How to manage roadmap and project milestones

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

# Agile Methodology

Agile methodology is a way to manage a project by breaking it into several phases.

&nbsp;

## Steps example

- Make a plan for 15 days
- Develop according to plan
- Test according to plan
- Take feedback from the customers
- Start next plan

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

# Agile Frameworks

- Scrum Framework
- Kanban Framework
- Extreme Programming

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

# Agile Principle

12 agile principles are -

1. Satisfy the customer
2. Welcome changing requirements
3. Deliver working software frequently
4. Business works with developer daily
5. Build project around motivated individuals
6. Face to face conversion best
7. Working software matters
8. Constant pace
9. High quality code is faster
10. Maximize work not done
11. Self-organizing team deliver quality
12. Feedback loops used to improve

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

# Agile Alternative

- Waterfall methodology
- Rapid development
- Lean etc.

